##KEYWORDS('algebra, absolute value sign')

DOCUMENT();     
loadMacros("PGbasicmacros.pl",     
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",     
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"    
);     

TEXT(beginproblem(),);

$a=random(1,19,1);
$b=random(2,9,1);

BEGIN_TEXT

This exercise concerns the definition of absolute values. Evaluate the following expressions: $BR
\(|-$a|= \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
\(-$a-|-$b|= \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
If \($a<x\), simplify the expression by removing the absolute sign $BR
\(|$a-x| = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
If \(y<-$b\), evaluate the expression$BR
\( \displaystyle \frac{|y+$b|}{y+$b} = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp( $a ) ); 

$diff=$a+$b;
$diff1=-$diff;

ANS(num_cmp( $diff1 ) );
ANS(str_cmp("x-$a") );
ANS(num_cmp( -1) );

ENDDOCUMENT();
